---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="Agent Format">
  <h1>Agent Format</h1>

  <p>Agents are single TypeScript files with a structured header and a SKILL.md docstring block.</p>

  <h2>File Structure</h2>
  <pre><code>// agent: pr_reviewer
// description: Reviews PRs for logic errors, style violations, and test coverage
// version: 3
// tools: gh_api, read_file, run_command
// input_schema: sample input schema
// output_schema: sample output schema

docstring block here (## SKILL.md)

import tools, handle from "agent-forge-runtime";

const INPUT_SCHEMA = &lcub; pr_url: "string", repo: "string" &rcub;;
const OUTPUT_SCHEMA = &lcub; issues: "array", score: "number", summary: "string" &rcub;;

async function handle(input: unknown): Promise&lt;unknown&gt; &lcub;
  const &lcub; pr_url, repo &rcub; = input as &lcub; pr_url: string; repo: string &rcub;;
  // ... agent logic
  return &lcub; issues: [], score: 0, summary: "" &rcub;;
&rcub;

export &lcub; handle &rcub;;</code></pre>

  <h2>Header Fields</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Required</th><th>Description</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr><td><code>agent</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>Unique agent name (kebab-case)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>description</code></td><td>string</td><td>Yes</td><td>One-line description of purpose</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>version</code></td><td>number</td><td>Yes</td><td>Version number (incremented by Refiner)</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>tools</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>No</td><td>List of tools the agent uses</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>input_schema</code></td><td>Record</td><td>Yes</td><td>Input parameter names and types</td></tr>
      <tr><td><code>output_schema</code></td><td>Record</td><td>Yes</td><td>Output field names and types</td></tr>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>SKILL.md Block</h2>
  <p>The docstring contains a <code>## SKILL.md</code> section parsed by output adapters. It includes:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Role</strong> — one sentence persona</li>
    <li><strong>Tools</strong> — TypeScript signatures for each tool used</li>
    <li><strong>Behavior</strong> — detailed instructions for the agent</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Handler Function</h2>
  <p>The handler function is the agent's entry point. It:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Receives input matching <code>INPUT_SCHEMA</code></li>
    <li>Uses tools from <code>agent-forge-runtime</code></li>
    <li>Returns output matching <code>OUTPUT_SCHEMA</code></li>
    <li>Handles errors gracefully, returning error info in output</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Runtime Package</h2>
  <p>Agents import tools from <code>agent-forge-runtime</code>:</p>
  <pre><code>import tools, handle from "agent-forge-runtime";</code></pre>
  <p>Available tools:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><code>read_file(path)</code></li>
    <li><code>run_command(cmd, cwd?)</code></li>
    <li><code>gh_api(endpoint, method?)</code></li>
    <li><code>grep(pattern, path)</code></li>
    <li><code>write_file(path, content)</code></li>
    <li><code>search_web(query)</code></li>
  </ul>
</Layout>
